    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00baC/ 220\u00baC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Deseed the<strong> peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly chop into bite-size pieces</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4] </span>pieces of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper and layer them over each other</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped peppers</strong> to the middle with the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the pepper to form 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2]</span> sealed parcel<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the pepper has softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the peppers are in the oven, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flaked almonds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Transfer the <strong>toasted almonds</strong> to a bowl and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until softened and lightly charred, then remove the pan from the heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pepper from the oven and add it a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>pepper juices</strong> from the tray</p><p>Then add the<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>toasted almonds</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and the juice from the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, then<strong> </strong>blitz until you have a coarse paste \u2013 this is your<strong> roasted red pepper sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the courgettes to the heat and once hot, add the <strong>roasted red pepper sauce</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>pitted black</strong> <strong>olives</strong> to the pan with the <strong>drained pasta</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and a generous crack of<strong> black pepper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up and cook for 2 min further \u2013 this is your <strong>saucy roasted red pepper & olive pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-saucy-roasted-red-pepper-and-olive-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>saucy</strong> <strong>roasted red pepper & olive pasta </strong>in bowls</p><p>Tear over the <strong>basil</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining toasted almonds</strong></p><p>Tip: Season to taste with a pinch more salt</p><p>Sorted!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
